===Etymology===
{{etyl|ar}} {{term|اسلام|إسْلام|sc=Arab|tr=‘islām|submission (to the will of God)|lang=ar}}. The root is the same as that of {{term|سلام|سَلام|sc=Arab|tr=salām||peace|lang=ar}}.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}}
{{wikipedia}}

# A [[monotheistic]] [[religion]] that originated with the teachings of the Prophet [[Muhammad]] ([[pbuh]]) having the same [[root]]s as [[Christianity]] and [[Judaism]]; its [[revelatory]] [[scripture]] is the [[Qur'an]]; its [[follower]]s are [[Muslim]].

